OL,5,Cdebt
OL,7,F"Bishop Eton states they unfortunately
OL,8,Fhad to employ an interim headteacher
OL,9,Ffor half a year at a cost of #33,500
OL,10,Fwhile the school was also having to
OL,11,Fpay the defendant's wages until June
OL,12,F2024, when he resigned. They cancelled
OL,13,Fplans to buy pupils' iPads due to the
OL,14,Fcost."
OL,16,FOliver Saddington, defending, said
OL,17,FMetcalf had committed the fraud after
OL,18,Fmaxing out his credit cards and
OL,19,Fspiralling into #100,000 of debt.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
